{
  "texts": [
    "The good news is that there is a fix: collect a sample of benchmark data using the existing measurement procedure and empirically model the LLM's error.",
    "The corollary of this fix is that economists should not use the LLM's output for plug-in estimation without this type of validation data and measurement error correction.",
    "To illustrate what guarantee is needed to use an LLM to solve an estimation problem, let us further formalize what we mean by an estimation problem.",
    "The researcher specifies some parameter of interest θ ∈Θ and a moment condition g(•) that, in principle, identifies this parameter.",
    "Consequently, if the researcher collected the economic concept by applying the existing measurement procedure f * (•) to each text piece r, she would be satisfied to calculate the parameter estimate"
  ]
}